## Normalized Test-Family Ledger

### Frozen Normalization Choices

- `[VERIFIED]` All four Step-4 families live on the same canonical one-bridge
  role-labeled helical packet
  `P_n = (A_n, B_n, C_n, D_n, E_n)`
  with mandatory conjugate completion.
- `[VERIFIED]` All four families are read on the same desired-channel ledger:
  `A -> B`,
  `A -> C`,
  `B,C -> C`,
  `C,A <-> D`,
  `D,D -> E`,
  together with the same forced spectator classes
  `mirror`,
  `companion`,
  `feedback`,
  `cross`.
- `[INFERRED]` The canonical gauge is:
  `|A_n(0)| = 1`,
  `arg A_n(0) = 0`,
  one frozen role order,
  one conjugate-representative convention,
  and one family-declared helical sign sheet.
- `[INFERRED]` Any family with nonzero on-template production is transported by
  the allowed whole-sheet exact scaling to the normalized activation window
  `I = [0, 1]`
  with
  `int_I D_on(t) dt = 1`.
  Families with
  `int_I D_on(t) dt = 0`
  are marked `inadmissible-static` and are not counted as positive witnesses.

