+# Refined Chain 03 - Repaired `F_SL(rho)` Provenance And Carried-Range Boundary
+
+## Central Premise
+
+After Step 8, the clean positive-facing branch is still repaired
+`G_tmpl`
+on the carried scale-separated family
+`F_SL(rho)`,
+but the open problem is narrower than the selected chain says.
+Step 6 already froze the live scope:
+the carried family question is whether
+`0 < rho <= 1/16`
+stays inside repaired
+`G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`
+on the fixed window
+`I = [0, 1]`
+with thresholds
+`(1/4, 49/256)`.
+
+So the real bottleneck is not a fresh family derivation from nothing.
+It is whether the Step-4 draft `F_SL(rho)` arithmetic can be promoted into
+same-currency theorem-grade data on the repaired Step-5 / Step-6 ledger.
+Until that promotion happens, no exact interval theorem is earned.
+And even if it happens, the honest output is only family-local template
+admissibility, not closure, leakage equivalence, or near-circuit realization.
+
+## Verifiable Result Target
+
+Either:
+
+- a repaired same-currency promotion of the `F_SL(rho)` defect ledger on the
+  carried range
+  `0 < rho <= 1/16`,
+  followed by a carried-range admissibility theorem with sharp boundary
+  `rho = 1/16`
+  if the promoted formulas support it;
+- a narrower witness-only memo showing that the repaired record supports
+  `rho = 1/16`
+  but not a full carried-range theorem; or
+- a bounded source-basis failure memo stating that the repository still lacks
+  theorem-grade repaired `rho`-dependent defect formulas.
+
+## Why This Chain Is Meaningfully Different
+
+This chain is not reopening the whole Step-4 family
+`0 < rho <= 1/12`,
+not defining a new closure object,
+and not trying to promote template passage into near-circuit behavior by
+rhetoric.
+It is a source-basis and boundary audit of one already-promoted Step-6 object.
+Its value is narrow but real:
+either the carried `F_SL(rho)` arithmetic can be upgraded into repaired theorem
+data, or the branch stops cleanly and says why.
+
+## Ordered Steps
+
+### Step 1 - Freeze Authority, Scope, And Non-Implication Up Front
+
+Depends on: none.
+
+Action: adopt Step-6 authority rather than re-freezing new foundations.
+Fix:
+the canonical packet sheet,
+repaired `G_tmpl`,
+thresholds `(1/4, 49/256)`,
+fixed window `I = [0, 1]`,
+and the carried domain
+`0 < rho <= 1/16`.
+
+Action: declare in advance that the old Step-4 root
+`(-3 + sqrt(10)) / 2`
+belongs only to unrepaired provenance on the old
+`lambda_spec = 1/4`
+sheet.
+It is not a live endpoint candidate in this repaired branch.
+
+Action: declare in advance that any success here is only a family-local
+template-admissibility statement unless an additional same-currency transfer
+lemma is actually proved.
+Do not infer leakage passage,
+closure,
+or near-circuit realization from template passage alone.
+
+Expected output: one authority memo citing the existing Step-6 freeze and the
+Step-8 no-overclaim warning.
+
+Kill condition: if the branch needs to reopen the wider Step-4 family
+`0 < rho <= 1/12`,
+retune thresholds,
+or treat unrepaired arithmetic as live repaired evidence, stop.
+
+### Step 2 - Run An Adversarial Promotion Audit On The Existing `F_SL(rho)` Ledger
+
+Depends on: Step 1.
+
+Action: audit the existing candidate formulas for
+`Delta_tmpl(rho)`
+and
+`Delta_spec(rho)`
+from the Step-4 pro-side report and its check script against the repaired
+Step-5 / Step-6 currency.
+Distinguish carefully between:
+stalled draft arithmetic,
+reproducibility checks,
+and promoted theorem authority.
+
+Action: require one explicit same-currency derivation or airtight citation path
+for the repaired family ledger.
+Keep desired-channel and spectator contributions separate so the repaired
+boundary computation does not rest on aggregated draft heuristics.
+
+Action: if the candidate formulas survive, record exactly what has been
+promoted and what remains unproved.
+If they do not survive, stop with a source-basis failure memo instead of
+pretending the branch still has an exact theorem path.
+
+Expected output: either one promoted repaired family ledger or one explicit
+source-basis failure memo.
+
+Kill condition: if the only support for the family ledger is the old draft log
+or a hand-entered checker without upgraded repaired-ledger authority, stop.
+
+### Step 3 - Solve Only The Carried-Range Boundary Problem
+
+Depends on: Step 2.
+
+Action: if Step 2 lands a promoted repaired ledger, solve the inequalities
+`Delta_tmpl(rho) <= 1/4`
+and
+`Delta_spec(rho) <= 49/256`
+only on the carried Step-6 domain
+`0 < rho <= 1/16`.
+
+Action: treat
+`rho = 1/16`
+as the live boundary candidate.
+Do not reactivate
+`(-3 + sqrt(10)) / 2`
+except as rejected unrepaired provenance.
+
+Action: distinguish carefully between:
+uniform admissibility on the carried range,
+sharpness at the carried endpoint,
+and the weaker outcome that only the explicit witness
+`rho = 1/16`
+is currently earned.
+
+Expected output: one carried-range theorem candidate or one corrected boundary
+memo.
+
+Kill condition: if any claimed endpoint depends on widening the domain beyond
+`1/16`,
+changing thresholds,
+or importing unproved asymptotic corrections, stop.
+
+### Step 4 - Audit Transfer Limits Before Packaging
+
+Depends on: Step 3.
+
+Action: compare the family-local template result against the Step-8 closure-side
+warning only to police scope.
+Use that comparison to stop overclaim, not to manufacture new family
+structure.
+
+Action: state explicitly whether the branch stops at repaired
+`G_tmpl`
+admissibility or whether any additional transfer statement has actually been
+proved on the same currency.
+
+Action: forbid language that turns template passage into closure relevance,
+leakage equivalence,
+or near-circuit behavior by suggestion alone.
+
+Expected output: one no-overclaim scope memo.
+
+Kill condition: if the branch needs an unproved closure or transfer premise in
+order to sound significant, stop.
+
+### Step 5 - Package The Strongest Honest Verdict
+
+Depends on: Step 4.
+
+Action: package exactly one of these outcomes:
+
+- a repaired carried-subfamily admissibility memo, likely with boundary
+  `rho = 1/16`;
+- a witness-only memo at
+  `rho = 1/16`; or
+- a source-basis failure memo.
+
+Action: state explicitly what remains open:
+promotion to the original Step-4 family,
+hostile-side family separation on the same repaired ledger,
+and any closure-relevant transfer beyond family-local template admissibility.
+
+Expected output: one comparison-ready verdict with no stale arithmetic and no
+scope inflation.
+
+Kill condition: if the final writeup presents cleaned-up Step-4 draft
+arithmetic as a broader theorem than the repaired record earns, the chain
+fails.
+
+## Presentable-Result Outlook
+
+Most likely presentable output:
+a bounded source-basis memo or a carried-range admissibility memo with endpoint
+`rho = 1/16`.
+
+Best-case output:
+a theorem-grade repaired family ledger plus a sharp carried-range boundary
+result.
+
+Least likely output:
+a theorem on the original Step-4 family
+`0 < rho <= 1/12`
+or any closure-relevant transfer theorem from this branch alone.

